caption: New halal restaurant alert! Chingri means Shrimp in Bangla, but nevertheless a creative name.  The design and decor is minimalist/simple but yet elegant. They have really adorable paintings on the wall. The wait staff and service was great. I forgot the waitresses name but she was very attentive. My mother had a throat problem so she was looking for a room temperature ginger ale and the waitress came out asking if the ginger ale she has was good enough. It wasn’t so the waitress went and warmed up the can and gave my mother the ginger ale can. Talk about going above and beyond!  Regarding the food, the food variety is unique and tastes great. Would highly recommend the Chingri fried rice dish - it consists of shrimp, beef AND chicken. Talk about a triple threat. The portion is good enough to feed two people I would say. The food also came out warm and didn’t take too long to come.  Overall would rate 5/5. Come out and enjoy/support this small business restaurant! You wont regret it!
I had received the wrong item from my order. I called and they sent the correct item over in less than 10 minutes, no questions asked. Also, their food is delicious.
Food was good and worth the value. Service can be fast or slow. That's why 4 stars.
They recently opened and for a location like Steinway where there are so many options, this was definitely one of the best, great food with great service and management.

I went yesterday  with lots of hope .ordered so many items . Oh my goddess the food was totally horrible. Every item was tasteless and smelled so bad .. we were so disappointed and upset .. I spend 100 dollar just for garbage. This restaurant should banned. Money is hard to make so I’m sure people can’t see throwing money direct to the garbage.

I was met with friendly service and hospitality. The manager and I built a connection immediately. Don't miss on appetizers, because they have a special sauce that will taste good with anything! The lamb chops are extremely savory and sweet, definitely recommend it. My boys and I truly enjoyed the service and food that this restaurant offers. Go there for special occasions, you won't regret it!
Really good food with really good portions and ambiance.

Been hearing about this restaurant for a while decided to check it out yesterday for dinner. Made reservations for 2 ppl at 7:30pm. Get there , we were checked in and temperature was taken. Tables were socially distanced. Place looked really nice had few tables seated in there. We started with the chingri appetizer combo which contained chicken lollipop, spring rolls and shrimp tempura. I was hoping the chicken lollipops would be more breaded but was still good. The Mocktails we ordered were Oasis and Paloma , they were excellent. Now to the main food , I had ordered the lamb chops they were cooked to perfection. Not many "Desi" restaurants know how to do that. My friend had ordered the Udon With Beef , she liked hers as well.  Also they brought out 2 desserts on the house !! We truly appreciated the gesture!!  Service- 10/10 Ambiance- 10/10 Parking - Street COVID 19 - Precautions were taken Outdoor Seating Available

High Expectation turned into disappointment. Food is expensive but tastes horrible. Dry satay, sweet and sour chicken tasted like cucumber went bad. Hard to chew sizzling beef. Special fried rice was okay. But overall lacked sufficient marination. The only thing good was the satay sauce. Won’t try this place again. Good customer service though. Sorry, we tried to like the food. But didn’t like it at all.

Went in with high expectations and got out with high disappointment. Dry satay, sweet and sour chicken tasted like cucumber went bad. Hard to chew sizzling beef. Special fried rice was okay. But overall lacked sufficient marination. The only thing good was the satay sauce. Won’t try this place again. Good customer service though. Sorry, we tried to like the food. But didn’t like it at all.
I like their hospitality,  the sizzling chicken was the most delicious among which dishes I ate.
I would like to give 3 stars because of their services and the environment.The test of food and quantity is not enough.Moreover,the price is high. They should focus on the quantity as well as taste .
Perfect customer service..good food...best Hot and sour soup
The food was superb and the environment was great too a must place to visit with friends and family
Food was very good 😌

The only item worth buying on their menu is the soda. Had a double loaded burger, which happened to be quintuple loaded with mustard. Perfect for someone that has a mustard obsession and a taste for overpriced and  terrible food .

I went to Chingri on a Saturday evening. I was greeted with a warm welcome. The atmosphere is really nice. Definitely a place to bring your significant other and/or family. Food is amazing and tastes authentic to me (i am non-asian). I like how they have thai dishes, indo-pak dishes and chinese dishes, as well as american. I order the pad kee maow where the noodles were made freshly. They provide good serving portions. The food is made in moderate time which allows time to enjoy their wonderful appetizers. The bathroom is very clean. Best of all, the food is halal! Amazing restaurant. I highly recommend. Located on the part of steinway thats not so hectic and busy.

Great food! However, the quantity can definitely improve for the appetizers. It's tasty and all, so you crave more, but they give too little, compared to other restaurants. The sauces are very flavorful.  My only complaint was them forgetting my 2 Thai iced teas for one of my orders. I double checked with the man before leaving, and he told me everything was there. Yet, when I got home, the 2 Thai iced teas were missing, and we were disappointed. It's the best thing to accompany Thai food, and we weren't satisfied with our food because our drinks were missing. So please, take everything into account next time. Apart from this, I would definitely recommend this place.
Great food would recommend, lovely staff!

Love their food and hospitality.Since it was very cold the owner literally offered us to go sit inside for couple minutes in order to feel warm (with mask and definitely social distance). I’d recommend 10/10.Worth my money

We visited here yesterday. Food was very tasty & wonderful customer service. They also have great outdoor dining. I will definitely come here again with my family and friends. Loved their curry items and sizzler beef. Very good. Definitely recommend to Visit here.
The food was beautiful presented, and temperature  of the food was really well. Chow mein tasted very good and had amazing flavor. Sizzle lamb wasn’t too good . The mango lassi was incredible.

Ordered the spicy beef Manchurian special, spicy chow mein noodle and crispy banana with ice cream. If you want something truly spicy and flavorful, this is so far the best choice I’ve come across in Astoria. My Indian spice level is up there with some of the hottest spices and I make my own, but it was NOTHING like theirs!! Hot AF! Loved the manchurian better.. between the two but next time will substitute beef for chicken, as the beef was a bit chewy.
Food are testy and highly satisfying. They care about gusts and very nice service. Highly recommend.

Everything about my experience at Chingri was amazing. The outdoor dining area was really cute and had a great ambiance, and the servers were so kind and accomodating. The food was DELICIOUS. For appetizers, I had fried momo, spring rolls, and chicken lollipops. It was my first time trying fried momo and chicken lollipops, and Chingri did not disappoint! I also had chicken udon kee maow, which was absolutely delicious. The sauce was terrific, and the udon was perfectly done. I loved the dish. At the end I had a Thai iced tea, and it was truly one of the best I'd had.  I 100% recommend stopping by and supporting this great restaurant!
Food was delicious,I like to come again Nd again, highly recommend
Excellent food and customer service !!!! Highly recommend .
🏆for service and food. True flavor. Fry ice cream was the best desert. My family had a great experience. Enjoy

I came here on thanksgiving with my family and the food was absolutely astonishing, and the service was exceptionally amazing. I had absolutely no problems and no complaints. The owner was so incredibly nice that he gave us a complimentary pineapple fried rice dish. I’ve never had food as great as this in my life, I definitely 100% recommend coming here.

Very good tasting food. The special fried rice  was spot on and fresh. The chicken lollipop was fantastic; The only drawback would be the sauce which is a bit on the thick side and doesn’t suit the chicken. Other than that the server was fantastic, she took our hectic order promptly and made no mistakes. Giver her a raise 🙌🏼
I tried few times their food.  Great food with reasonably price.
Very nice, good taste good with nice serving, happy to eat there
Amazing food and great ambience!
we order food and its really amazing..i give five stars keep it up guys..8 people eat this food and all are belong to different nationalities and all are agree on it that its very good food

The server (Miriam) who seated us was so kind! The atmosphere is very calming in here. The spring rolls were delicious, however the rest of the food was mediocre. The chicken strips were bland. The chicken lollipop’s sauce was amazing. The salmon and the lamb were good but not worth a drive out for. The mocktails were extremely sour so I had to keep asking for a change. The green curry was not my favorite. The rice were bland as well. If you happen to be in the neighborhood then def try them out.

The best Thai food I have eaten. Great service, good ambience, the owner is extra courteous and nice. I tried chingri combo appetizer, spicy tom yum soup, manchurian special, pad kee maow, Penang curry. Everything was super delicious. Can't choose a clear favorite. Everything was flavory, strong, not that spicy (Indian standards). To top this meal the desert was a fried ice cream, the best I have ever eaten.

Must say that this place is hands down one of best new places in the area. Great options in the menu to choose from and they serve amazing non-alcoholic drinks.  We order few items along with three ribeye steaks. We wanted our steaks medium well, but it was over cooked. Still, it was delicious. We didn’t complain but the chef personally apologized and gave us two original steak dishes which was above and beyond. We were humbled that chef noticed this and made an attempt to make up for it. The staffs were friendly and attentive. If you’re in this area, I would 100% recommend to give them a try. I must mention that their entire menu is 100% certified halal.

Probably one of the best services I’ve received at a restaurant. The food was also very flavorful and delicious. The owner himself came out to make sure everything was good and made accommodations for food substitutions that were not part of the menu.

I really loved the Chingri Appetizer Combo and the Chingri Special Fried Rice and the Pineapple Fried Rice. We also ordered the Chow Mein Noodle, which I did not reorder because it was too oily/greasy for my liking.  The reason why I give this place 3 stars is because I reordered the Chingri Appetizer Combo which I did indeed enjoy but that’s it! The Chingri Special Fried Rice was disgusting!!! The rice was old, which I can tell because the rice was really stale and really dry. The vegetables were hard, so either they became stale or they weren’t steamed long enough. To make it worse, there were eggshells in my food! I took a bite and the bite was crunchy, I immediately became grossed out and spit out an eggshell and found more egg shells in my food.  I’m really disappointed because I had an excellent first experience and loved the food and I had a horrible second experience, which was the complete opposite of my wonderful first experience. I don’t think I’ll be reordering because it was a gross second experience!
Delicious food, fast clean and safe. Shrimp 🍤 tempura very delicious as were the entrees. Best of all has to be the great service and staff. Very informative and kind. Can't wait to be heading back 👌
Food was amazing, best customer service .we were well satisfied with our food definitely will go back .
Their foods were amazing, loved all the dishes!
Ver delicious food and awesome service
Best customer service ever!!! Highly recommend this place
One of the best Halal Thai in town. Pineapple fried rice and mango lassi is out of the world. Menu is reasonably priced. Very clean premises and best customer service compared other halal restaurants
Awful terrible

We had such a great experience here for our first time. They truly give timely, excellent service. Very kind and hospitable staff.  The Chicken Lollipop and fried homemade Momos were excellent. The spicy mayo will surprise you, it’s not the typical sauce but even better with what appears to be a cumin masala blend. Sooo good. The fry on both appetizers was light and crispy.  We got the Chingri special fried rice and Chicken basil fried rice. I personally preferred the flavor of the basil fried rice but the chingri special fried rice has a variety of proteins. Both were cooked well. Portions are filling for one person. If I could add any feedback, I think it would be even better with some more heat/chili but of course that is up to your own taste.  Lastly,  we tried the fried ice cream. The crust was a bit hard but still tasted excellent. Would recommend to share this with someone as it is large!  They also served us a very nice Thai iced tea 👌🏽Light and not overly sweet.  Will definitely be coming back! 😊
Nice restaurant, HMS certifies, good food, and good service
Great Food ! Great Service !

Went out with some friends for dinner. I was skeptical at first because my experience with Asian fusion places aren’t great. However, every dish we ordered was actually really good. I had the Pad Thai which was so very flavorful and some other amazing dishes included the Tom Yum soup, sizzling lamp chops, and the pineapple fried rice. Also, the food is served aesthetically, so it is perfect for instagramming. The chef also came out and said hi to us, which I thought was beautiful and made the experience much more personal. Also the ambiance and decor of the restaurant is very nice. I never write reviews but I thought this one worth it!
Very Tasty food, and friendly service. I ordered their manchurian special and rib eye stake. It was amazing. Definitely coming back

Me and my friends came here last week and we absolutely loved the food! The appetizer combo, pad Thai and fried rice was amazing 10/10. Just don’t get the pina colada drink it was so bad. It tasted not fresh at all! Other than that I can’t wait to come back and try the rest of the food !

Great food, we had soup with shrimp, spicy and with great flavor. Then we had the special, a great steak with an amazing lemon-coconut based soup. This is a great place, classy, clean, and great service.
Food was tasty , good service. we all got noodles pretty tents to sit in outside for outdoor dining

I try my best not to rate anyone bad cuz it’s business and do not want to hurt it. . But we drove from Long Island to there and were excited. But left with disappointment and didn’t even finish the food. . . Piña colds, horrible. . Only taste was pineapple juice . . Mojito disgusting. Food we ordered, ate few spoons smelled horrible, rotten( we could’ve made a scene and get new order, but so many customers around, so we stayed quite.  ,) but we decided to leave the food as is, didn’t pack it to go. . Asked for check, paid and left. Never again . . All the hype for nothing. Went to Greek gyro stand truck on the corner and loved it instead.
Nothing crazy about it other than the 1 hour wait time.
Great Food but honestly even better service!!
the staff went above and beyond to provide amazing service. the food was delicious as well -- the pineapple fried rice was definitely the highlight
The food was amazing, like not just good, it was phenomenal and the staff is super nice and friendly, food came out super fast. Thumps up .
Food, service and environment was awesome!!
Great customer service and amazing food!

Can we take a moment for the impeccable customer service. The hospitality was amazing. The food was amazing. The soup was ok, both fried rice and udon kee mao (not sure if this is the exact name) was perfectly spiced and had a good amount of meat. The size of the chicken lollipops were super tiny however it tasted great. Shrimp and spring rolls tasted good too. Overall the food was great and I like a place where I’m treated right with respect. Not to mention I was also given a complimentary Ice coffee at the end which was a great surprise as well.

Can we take a moment for the impeccable customer service. The hospitality was amazing. The food was amazing. The soup was ok, both fried rice and udon kee mao (not sure if this is the exact name) was perfectly spiced and had a good amount of meat. The size of the chicken lollipops were super tiny however it tasted great. Shrimp and spring rolls tasted good too. Overall the food was great and I like a place where I’m treated right with respect. Not to mention I was also given a complimentary Ice coffee at the end which was a great surprise as well.
Loved the food!!
Amazing food and service perfect for family.
Honestly the food quality is off the chart. Amazing service and again loved each and every dish. It was just amazing.  See you again soon!
Overpriced low quality and quantity food
Best customer service ever
Trust me, I usually don’t give ratings, but this is the best customer service,
Went here with my family multiple times and the food is sooo yummy! I love the fish cakes and spicy basil fried rice. Can't wait to go again and try more stuff from the menu :)
Food was great! Great chef. I would definitely go again and recommend to everyone I know

It was seven of us. We all had a great time. We ate outside.  Their setup is one of the two best that I have seen, even feeling as if somehow we were inside.  The food was delicious. I had their pineapple fried rice, served in an open pineapple. Amazing presentation.  The service was fantastic (Anlize). Extremely happy to be introduced to this wonderful place. I will definitely dine here again.  After meeting the chef, my one recommendation was a vegan pumpkin custard.  He says he will work on it for me. Such a humble person.
Just ordered take out from here and everything was delicious! The green curry was one of the best I have ever had. The food was ready on time and the staff were very kind. Will definitely come again.
Over priced food, very small portion, very bad service. Please review your bill they made mistake on our table and the next table too.
Good customer service. But food quantity was too small for the price, and we ordered soup and personally I'd say it tasted really bad.
I had a bad experience with bad service. my order took more than an hour and I was not happy with the quality

The service was really bad. I made a reservation for a Sunday and I had to make the reservation twice. For some reason, they couldn’t find my reservation and told me I had to wait. They said they’d give me a call when they have a table ready. 45 minutes pass and I don’t get a call so me and my friends decide to walk back and the “host” sees us and sits us down. He says sorry for not calling. After we’re seated, they took a really long time to give us menus, a really long time to take our order, and a really long time for appetizers and entrees to arrive. All in all really bad experience. I came here because muslimfoodies rated this place 9/10 but I will never listen to muslimfoodies ever again. It was not 9/10, it was just bad. The guy who was our waiter was so sarcastic, very rude, and had an attitude that made me even more mad. It took 30 minutes for our appetizers to arrive and then an additional 30 minutes for our entrees to arrive. Another guy who seemed like the manager tried guilt tripping my table into eating a salad after we kindly requested that they take it away. My friend did not like the smell of the larb salad and was on the verge of throwing up, so we asked for them to take it away, he kept insisting that we keep it on the table. He guilt tripped us by saying "if you don't eat it, we're just gonna throw it away and it’ll get wasted so please just keep it." Very disgusting and unprofessional. This is the worst experience I've had in a restaurant ever. I understand you guys are new but if you keep doing things like this, I don't expect you guys to stay open much longer.
Food was good, service was great. I do think the portions were just a little small but still overall great experience.
We found this place mistakenly. Great food and an awesome service. Will certainly come here again soon.
Great food

The food here was delicious ! Everything fresh and very nice presentation ... the pineapple fried rice was awesome and the fried ice cream incredible! We had a great time with our friend Nahid today ! We will come back soon definitely...
The food was really good ...... We enjoyed it 😊

Took my friend here and we had Thai iced tea + spicy margarita + shrimp tempura + sizzling rack of lamb & pad Thai. Food was absolutely amazing! Drink was on point! I had to order spicy margarita twice and service 10/10!! I would go there again!!

Probably the best Halal Asian fusion restaurant in Queens. Appetizers taste delicious especially chicken satay, shrimp tempura and spring rolls are outstanding. Pineapple fired-rice and sizzling lamb is new favorite for me. I would recommend this restaurant 100%

Worst experience I ever had at a restaurant. I understand this is a new restaurant and its a new experience, but the experience of dining needs significant improvement. We reserved a table 8 hours in advanced and were not seated accordingly under the tent.. also waited 2 hours for our food!!! The food tasted bland, most of it having no flavor or way beneath our expectations. It was pricy as well and this place is nothing but OVERHYPED.  You would expect to be treated fairly while coming to a restaurant but that was not the case here. If I could give less than one star, I would but theres no option for that. You're way better off going somewhere else in Astoria theres much better options than here.
It was a wonderful experience. The food was exquisite! Definitely recommend the chow mein. I will surely be coming here again!
Great customer service! Good food and vibes!
Food was absolutely delicious. Highly recommend the shrimp tempura! Staff is also very kind!
Food is not good

Great new place in Astoria! Excellent food, excellent service, great concept. They've launched at a challenging time but hopefully they become a go-to spot in the neighborhood. Highly recommended; I'll be going back.
Great mixed fried rice and paad thai.
Owner Moynul Bhai very friendly.i went there from Virginia he took care of me very well .food are so good .
Amazing service and food. Just a heads up the food is very hot 🔥 so beware. Overall excellent food! The hosts are extremely helpful and thoughtful. Had a great time with family.
excellent customer service

بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم  Mash’Allāh, the food was absolutely delicious. I got the Sizzling Lamb Rack with medium sauce and the “extra hot” on the side. For a desi, the extra hot is 100% worth the try; not overbearingly spicy and quite flavorful! The lamb itself was perfectly cooked, not gamey and very filling when paired with the garlic rice, which was a first for me, a subtle hint of garlic in the rice made it a perfect pair.  I did try the chicken and beef sizzler from my colleagues, the meat was flavorful and tender - unfortunately they didn’t share more for me to give a longer review on it hahaha.  The lollipop chicken and the sauce is by far the best I’ve had; better than Sagar and Tangra - which are the only other places I’ve had them.  I had the pleasure with speaking with Masood (forgive me if I spelled it wrong) one of the owners, very humble gentlemen. He gave me salams and asked for du’a; May Allāh put barakāh in the business and your time, Allāhumma ameen (say ameen if you’ve read this far).  The workers all practiced all health safeties and very friendly; definitely look forward to trying more items! Jazak’Allāh khāir.

I LOVED everything I ordered from CHINGRI in Astoria. It’s hard to find halal Thai good , but it’s harder to find GOOD Thai food- so here it is!! Disclaimer: Mouth watering food. Hehe  Sizzling rack of lamb, pineapple fried rice ( on an actual pineapple! 🤗 ) & chicken lollipop.  The setup is super cute & the customer service was impeccable. Everything was beyond my expectations. The owner was really sweet! The servers were also great!
Kool

This spot is open for dine in . They have nice cozy outdoor seating. The day I visited it was their first day.  We tried all  the mocktails from the menu and I personally liked Oasis.  For appetizers I would give them 5/5 .We tried 4 appetizers (Thai Satay, Chicken Lollypop, Shrimp Tempura, Homemade Momo) and all of them came out very good. Dipping sauces for appetizers tasted amazing.  Now come to the main dishes here I think  Pad Kee Maw will take me back to the restaurant again and again. Red curry and Fried rice are also up to the mark .We also had beef Manchurian, it was ok but could have been better. Portion for the Entrées are good for 2 people.  We had  fried banana with ice -cream for dessert and it was great.

Their red and green Thai curries are really good and ample in portions for 2-3 persons – additionally their Green Tea Ice Cream is also very good – one of the few places in NYC I have tried. Their customer service is 5 stars, from the server to owners all were very polite and went the extra mile to make sure we were happy with everything. They also treated us with a desert on the house.
This place is a must if you are in Astoria! The food is incredibly delicious and the portions are very generous. The staff is friendly and welcoming making the experience worth it all

Have been there multiple times past their friends and family event pre-launch and the food gets better each time!  From a very caring head chef for the quality of food he puts out to the very friendly staff and management.  Great out door seating, very clean, and well amazing food !
There food so good and best service !
If I could put more than 5 stars I would. The service was very good and so was the food. I will be back very soon. If your in Astoria you should definitely stop by !

Really tremendous meal and a very warm welcome – we would recommend this amazing restaurant and will try to go back again. Excellent environment, friendly service, great menu choices, and really decent food and at affordable prices. Will be back.

Great food and extremely courteous staff! Overall, a great experience. The waitress recommended her own personal favorite which was the fried dumplings and her recommendation was definitely on point. Those dumplings were awesome! It didn’t take long for the food to arrive and it came in hot, fresh and steaming! Highly recommend this restaurant, I’ll definitely visit again.
Delicious foods wrapped with warm hospitality in a beautiful location!

Went to dinner here with my wife within a week of it opening. They had outdoor seating, under a tent as well as around the restaurant entrance. The service was excellent and the staff was especially courteous. The dishes are a mix of Bengali, Thai and other east Asian flavors. I recommend the Shrimp Tempura. One really cool thing they had was non-alcoholic mocktails -- I really liked the mojito. The portions were large in my opinion, we couldn't finish it all and had to take some to-go with us. I would definitely come back here again!
The food and service were amazing! Susannah, the employee serving us was also incredibly nice and attentive. A wonderful experience overall.

Their food was honestly very immaculate!!! A halal asian fusion spot is just what Astoria needed and they did not disappoint! Their mocktails were yummy and satisfying to drink while sitting in their cute outdoor seating area that btw was decorated beautifully!!!  A family friendly location on Steinway street (the heart of Astoria) with food that leaves you wanting to come back :) 10/10 recommend definitely try it out !

My visit to Chingri Restaurant was one of my most memorable outings! The outdoor dining space was lovely; the ambiance created by the candles and flowers atop our tables provided a warm and welcoming environment. The food was incredible! As other reviews have mentioned, the Mango lassi is a MUST! Shrimp chow mein (I prefer my food spicy so the range of spice offered is extremely helpful) is UNFORGETTABLE - I am still thinking about it! The chicken lollipops, shrimp tempura, and spring rolls are the best appetizers/starters to a wonderful meal, however, there are a variety of appetizers that are offered. These are the appetizers I tasted as I ordered the appetizer combo. The desserts are also delicious, the restaurant staff was gracious enough to treat us to dessert on the house the day of our visit. This is a memory I will never forget and makes you want to return. I will certainly be back and am excited to try new dishes! Hope this Restaurant nothing but the best - Congratulations on the opening! I feel so grateful to have this new restaurant in town serving Zabiha certified Halal meat - not something you see often.
Awesome food and service.

I decided to take my mother for a dinner date...and  I was surprised that she enjoyed her sizzled salmon with vegetables along with the garlic rice that was served! While I enjoyed my plate of fried rice with chicken (basic but delicious) alongside a mango lassi! The inside of the place was decorated with beautifully painted artworks representing the background of the family that owned the business. All the staff were very welcoming and provided a wonderful and accommodating service as we ordered our plates. Can't wait to go back with my family and friends!
Food was really good. Got the pad see ew, chow mein both with beef and loved it! Really fresh, reasonable prices, great customer service. Would def come back.
Too expensive..

I really enjoyed dining at Chingri Restaurant! My friends and I were greeted by the sweetest employees who ensured we had the best experience possible. It was only my second time trying chicken lollipop and it did not disappoint. It was flavorful and delicious. I've had pad see ew at many places and the one at Chingri was amazing! It was tasty and the noodles were perfect. Of course I had to try the Thai iced tea along with my meal. It was sweet and refreshing. I'm looking forward to returning to Chingri and trying out some new dishes! Stop by for a delicious meal and a great time with family or friends!!

The food is amazing and delicious. One of the best tasting indo-chinese I’ve had. Only reason for 4 stars is because of price-to-portion ratio. The portion is a bit too less for the price and also compared to other similar restaurants. If the portion were to increase, I’d definitely buy it more often. Still highly recommend.

Wanted to stop by for a while, so finally came in and grabbed some takeout. Got momos, chicken lollipop and tried out the Thai ice tea and mango lassi. Everything was so fresh and delicious. The chicken lollipop was AMAZING, the sauce had the perfect balance of sweet spicy with a kick to it! The drinks were really good, the lassi had the perfect consistency not too thick or too liquid. Overall loved the food, will be stopping by again to try more of the dishes ! 😍
Good food

this is a new Asian Fusion restaurant called Chingri that opened up in Astoria 8 days ago. Its 100% halal. For starters we got Momos and Spring Rolls. They were equally delicious. For drinks we had gotten mocktails. The Oasis and Mojito. Entrees were beef chow mein and chicken chow mein, beef and chicken pad thai, and chicken with broccoli, and thai green curry with coconut rice. Each dish was made to everyone’s requested spice level and we were pleasantly surprised as to how amazing it all tasted. For dessert we got fried matcha ice cream and fried bananas with a scoop of matcha ice cream. Service was good and the employees were so kind and accommodating. Also, they have outdoor seating so it wasn’t bad at all.  Overall, i’d give this place a 10/10. Please check this place out! It’s definitely worth all the hype! 😍
Honestly this place is one of the best restaurants I have ever been to!! Their food is bomb.com and the employee’s are really amazing. Their customer service is on point. I would go there again.
Amazing food. Definitely going back again.A++
Nicely served, like the out look. Well done and wish you best of luck.
Proper fusion South Asian Fusion Food. Comfort. Missed this in New York coming in from Toronto.
Really good Halal Thai food.
Food was awesome and the environment was cool too. Desserts were 🔥🔥
One of the best Authentic halal food we had so far in New York, highly recommended.
Food was great. Loved it!

I was really excited to try this new Restaurent. The food is very delicious. Hands down the best chicken lollipop I had in a long time. Chicken pad Thai was very tasty compare to other places where extra sauce makes it less tasty.  Fried ice cream is out of the world.
Food was amazing, customer service was excellent, and the mango lassi at the end of our meal was divine. Will definitely come here again!

Great food! I was there for a pre-launch event and they have a great menu with a variety of Thai inspired dishes. The food was tasty and flavorful and the servers were very pleasant, too. I took a chance and ordered the crispy fried banana for my dessert and it was amazing! I would definitely come back here.
